<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName LSID="MB826797" authority="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Erythrogloeaceae" genus="Dendrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrostoma castaneicola" order="Diaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="castaneicola">Dendrostoma castaneicola C.M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="8" pageNumber="75">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Figure 5
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Dendrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrostoma castaneicola" order="Diaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="castaneicola">Dendrostoma castaneicola</taxonomicName>
differs from the two phylogenetically closely related species, 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. castaneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="castaneae">D. castaneae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. shaanxiense" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="shaanxiense">D. shaanxiense</taxonomicName>
, by its white central column.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="holotype">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
CHINA. Hebei Province: Chengde City, chestnut plantation, 
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="40.40889">40°24'32&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="117.48194">117°28'55&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 262 m a.s.l., on branches of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Fagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollissima">Castanea mollissima</taxonomicName>
, 28 Apr. 2018, N. Jiang &amp; C.M. Tian (holotype: BJFC-S1551; ex-type culture: CFCC 52743).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
Castaneicola, referring to the host genus, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanea" order="Fagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Castanea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="76" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
<pageBreakToken pageId="9" pageNumber="76" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
Sexual morph not observed. Asexual morph: Conidiomata pycnidial, conical to pulvinate, occurring separately, reddish-orange, semi-immersed in bark, 300-550 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
high, 900-1600 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diam.; wall of several layers of faint yellow textura angularis; central column beneath the disc more or less conical, white. Conidiophores reduced to conidiogenous cells. Conidiogenous cells lining the inner walls of the cavity, hyaline, smooth, subcylindrical to ampulliform, 5-14 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Conidia hyaline, aseptate, smooth, multiguttulate, thin-walled, ellipsoid to fusoid, straight, (9.3
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)10.5–12.8(–">-)10.5-12.8(-</normalizedToken>
13.8) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(3.1
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)3.2–3.8(–">-)3.2-3.8(-</normalizedToken>
4.1) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, l/w = (2.3
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)3–4(–">-)3-4(-</normalizedToken>
4.4) (n = 50).
</paragraph>
