<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="76" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="76">Culture characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="76">On PDA, cultures are initially white, becoming black after 2 weeks. The colonies are flat with irregular edge; texture uniform, producing a circle with faint orange conidiomata distributed along the edge of the circle within 1 month at 25 °C in the dark.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
